"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-05-djokovic-wins-olympic-gold-complete-career-golden-slam\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France (AFP) - Novak Djokovic defeated Carlos Alcaraz on Sunday to claim a maiden Olympic title and become just the fifth player to complete a career Golden Slam.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5810907891276308, \"rank\": 0.5697832575501527, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 46, \"end\": 60, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PARIS\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 5}, {\"ngram\": \"AFP\", \"from\": 15, \"to\": 18}, {\"ngram\": \"Novak Djokovic\", \"from\": 22, \"to\": 36}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 64, \"to\": 70}, {\"ngram\": \"a maiden Olympic title\", \"from\": 80, \"to\": 102}, {\"ngram\": \"just the fifth player\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 135}, {\"ngram\": \"a career Golden Slam\", \"from\": 148, \"to\": 168}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 37-year-old Serb, competing in his fifth Games, came through 7-6 (7/3), 7-6 (7/2) in an enthralling final at Roland Garros to add Olympic gold to his 24 Grand Slam triumphs.\", \"from\": 171, \"to\": 348, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 187, \"end\": 191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbs\", \"score\": 0.7639867483676667, \"rank\": 0.3089181411981353, \"text\": \"Serb\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbs\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his fifth Games\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 221}, {\"ngram\": \"an enthralling final\", \"from\": 260, \"to\": 280}, {\"ngram\": \"Roland Garros\", \"from\": 284, \"to\": 297}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic gold\", \"from\": 305, \"to\": 317}, {\"ngram\": \"his 24 Grand Slam triumphs\", \"from\": 321, \"to\": 347}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Victory allowed him to join Andre Agassi, Rafael Nadal, Steffi Graf and the watching Serena Williams as the only players to win all four Grand Slam tournaments and Olympic singles gold.\", \"from\": 350, \"to\": 535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 378, \"end\": 390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andre_Agassi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andre Agassi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andre_Agassi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andre_Agassi\"}, {\"begin\": 392, \"end\": 404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafael Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 406, \"end\": 417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steffi_Graf\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steffi Graf\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steffi_Graf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steffi_Graf\"}, {\"begin\": 435, \"end\": 450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Serena Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\"}, {\"begin\": 493, \"end\": 497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Slam_of_Curling\", \"score\": 0.999999906840462, \"rank\": 9.315947121809907e-08, \"text\": \"Slam\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Slam_of_Curling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Slam_of_Curling\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Victory\", \"from\": 350, \"to\": 357}, {\"ngram\": \"the only players\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 470}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic singles gold\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 534}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also became the oldest singles champion since tennis returned to the Olympics in 1988 and shattered Alcaraz's bid to add gold to the French Open and Wimbledon titles he has already pocketed this summer.\", \"from\": 537, \"to\": 742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 640, \"end\": 647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 0.9999999999554348, \"rank\": 3.0059771806688435e-11, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the oldest singles champion\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 579}, {\"ngram\": \"tennis\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 592}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 617}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 665}, {\"ngram\": \"the French Open and Wimbledon titles\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 705}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An emotional Djokovic celebrated by holding aloft the Serbian flag on court before clambering into the players' box to embrace his wife and children.\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 893, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 798, \"end\": 810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_Serbia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Serbian flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_Serbia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An emotional Djokovic\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 765}, {\"ngram\": \"court\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 819}, {\"ngram\": \"the players' box\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 859}, {\"ngram\": \"his wife\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 879}, {\"ngram\": \"children\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 892}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We almost played three hours, the final shot was the only moment when I was sure I could win the match,\\\" said Djokovic, who had lost heavily to Alcaraz in the Wimbledon final last month.\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 1082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1006, \"end\": 1014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6646463230300516e-19, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 1040, \"end\": 1047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 0.9999999999554348, \"rank\": 3.0059771806688435e-11, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"three hours\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 924}, {\"ngram\": \"the final shot\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 940}, {\"ngram\": \"the only moment\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 960}, {\"ngram\": \"the match\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 998}, {\"ngram\": \"the Wimbledon final\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1070}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I put my body, my family on the line to win gold and finally I did it.\\\"\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1156, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my body\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1098}, {\"ngram\": \"my family\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1109}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1121}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1133}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alcaraz was distraught and wept as he attempted to conduct a TV interview.\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1158, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 0.9999999999554348, \"rank\": 3.0059771806688435e-11, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a TV interview\", \"from\": 1217, \"to\": 1231}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Three hours, a big battle with tough moments,\\\" said the 21-year-old after a final in which neither player dropped serve.\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1355, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a big battle\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1260}, {\"ngram\": \"tough moments\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1279}, {\"ngram\": \"neither player\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's very painful to lose.\\\"\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Djokovic carved out a break point in the second game of the opener and three more in the fourth, all saved by the Spaniard.\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1500, \"end\": 1508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spaniards\", \"score\": 0.6163905828882268, \"rank\": 0.622347176479119, \"text\": \"Spaniard\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spaniards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spaniards\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Djokovic\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1394}, {\"ngram\": \"a break point\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1419}, {\"ngram\": \"the second game\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1438}, {\"ngram\": \"the opener\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1452}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then it was the Serb's turn to demonstrate his famed powers of resilience, fighting off three break points in the fifth game and another five in a marathon ninth game.\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1678, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1527, \"end\": 1531, \"title\": \"http://d